  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Coffee cooperative business development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project activities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Increasing youth in coffee farming activities: Mobilization events.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Exchange visit for coffee farmers&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;External financial audit for Abakundakawa Rushashi&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Developing strategic plan&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dissemination of organic farming practices&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advisory services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Female leadership training&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Follow up -Skills implementation on organic coffee farming ToT&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Participating in agriculture show&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;Abakundakawa is a primary coffee cooperative located in the highlands of the Northern Rwanda in Gakenke District. It started in 1999 as an association with 112 members and registered as cooperative in 2004 with 672 members.Currently the cooperative has 2136 members. The cooperative is involved in collecting cherries from members  pulping  washing  fermenting  sorting  drying and transportation to the dry mill. The cooperative plans to increase coffee production by increasing number of trees using organic manure. Since 2018 Agriterra is supporting the cooperative to reach its main goal of producing organic coffee and increasing the cooperative members with focus on youth.&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
